frameDefinitions: A Factor affects the outcome of an Undertaking, which  can be a goal-oriented activity or the maintenance of a desirable state, the work in a Field, or something portrayed as affecting an Interested_party.
An Experiencer can be described as having an emotion as induced by a Stimulus.
The Denoted_quantity is (generally) an imprecise characterization of the quantity of Individuals or a Mass, made with reference to a relatively easily and precisely imaginable Reference_quantity.
A Complainer communicates their negative emotional reaction to some state of affairs in a Complaint to an Addressee.
An Exerter, Action, or Force is capable of exerting or does exert a physical force at a level specified by the target.

A Speaker talks about a Topic, which may be an action performed by the Speaker or an entity or state of affairs that they are associated with in order to suggest that the Speaker is worthy of admiration.
frameExamples: Temperature is the most <t>critical</t> factor in successful storage.
The children <t>enjoyed</t> noise games and sing-songs.
It took <t><fex name='Denoted_quantity'>about</fex></t> three hours, but we 're done now.
The top US commander in Iraq <t>complained</t> to the Pentagon last winter that his supply situation was so poor that it threatened Army troops' ability to fight.
Eugenie loved the sea and was a <t>strong</t> swimmer.
Turkish officials <t>boasted</t> of giving 'tens of thousands of dollars in surreptitious payments' to a prominent American politician.
listRoleDefinitions: <fen>Factor</fen> is used for the concrete or abstract entity whose importance is assessed.
The <fen>Undertaking</fen> is a process or state or field of activity in which the <fen>Interested_party</fen> has a stake.
<fen>Interested_party</fen> identifies the people who are affected by a particular <fen>Factor</fen>.
A <fen>Factor</fen> may be generally important to the people or the activities in a field of endeavour.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Factor</fen> is important to the <fen>Undertaking</fen>.
The location at which the <fen>Factor</fen> is important.
The <fen>Experiencer</fen> is the person or sentient entity that experiences or feels the emotions.
The <fen>Stimulus</fen> is the person, event, or state of affairs that evokes the emotional response in the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Experiencer</fen> has an emotion as caused by the <fen>Stimulus</fen>.
The quantity denoted by phrases headed by the Target.
A substance that is being quantified.
A collection of entities, either quantifiable physical beings (e.g. <m>toads</m>) or quantifiable units whether physical or not (e.g. <m>dollars</m>).
A relatively precise quantity in some oft-used form that is used as the basis for defining the <fen>Denoted_quantity</fen>.
The <fen>Complainer</fen> is the sentient entity that produces the <fen>Complaint</fen> (whether spoken or written).
The lamentable situation that the <fen>Complainer</fen> is communicating to the <fen>Addressee</fen>.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is the subject matter to which the <fen>Complaint</fen> pertains.
<fen>Medium</fen> is the physical entity or channel used by the <fen>Complainer</fen> to transmit the <fen>Complaint</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the complaint is made.
This role specifies the location where the complaining takes place.
The <fen>Exerter</fen> that can or does exert a force of the level specified by the target.
The <fen>Force</fen> that can or does exert a force of the level specified by the target.
The <fen>Action</fen> that can or does exert a force of the level specified by the target.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Exerter</fen>, <fen>Action</fen>, or <fen>Force</fen> can or does exert its force.
The location where the <fen>Exerter</fen>, <fen>Action</fen>, or <fen>Force</fen> can or does exert its force.
The <fen>Speaker</fen> is the person who produces a message about a <fen>Topic</fen>.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is a positively judged entity or state of affairs with which the <fen>Speaker</fen> is associated and about which they talk.
<fen>Medium</fen> is the physical entity or channel used by the <fen>Speaker</fen> to transmit the statement.
A description of the state of affairs that redounds to the <fen>Speaker</fen>'s credit
<fen>Expressor</fen> is the body part or action that conveys the feeling of pride of the <fen>Speaker</fen>.
The time when the statement is made.
The role specifies the place where the statement takes place.
